Let's learn how to play "That's Not a Hat." Deal a gift card face up in front of each player and place the rest of the cards face up in a draw pile in the middle of the table to form a gift shop. →
Be sure to pay attention to which card is in front of each player. →
To start, the first player draws a new gift from the gift shop and shows that card to everyone. →
The card is then flipped over and is passed to the player indicated by the arrow on the back of the card. →
As the player passes the gift, they identify the card out loud saying, "I have a nice blank for you." In this case, it's an egg. →
The player receiving the gift now has two options. →
Accept the gift or refuse it. →
If the player receives the gift, they say thank you and places the card face down above their original gift card in front of them. →
And since it would be rude to re-gift a new gift, the next player gives away their original gift and leaves the new gift in front of them face down. →
When a player believes the gift is not correctly identified, they should refuse the gift and say, "That's not a blank." Then the player flips over the card and reveals the gift. →
Whichever player is wrong takes the card and places it face up in their personal discard pile as a penalty point. →
The player who receives the penalty point must draw a new gift from the gift shop. →
The game ends when one player receives three penalty points. →
Whoever has the lowest score wins the game. →
And that's how you play "That's Not a Hat." (soft music) (mysterious music) (tavern music) →
